text: Dženan Ćatić (born May 26, 1992) is a Bosnian-American http://www.mlssoccer.com/news/article/2015/03/05/rookie-dzenan-catic-living- his-american-dream-philadelphia-union footballer. ==Career== ===College and Youth=== He attended East Kentwood High School. After graduation he spent time with the youth team and second team of German club 1. FC Kaiserslautern, Catic moved back to the United States to play NAIA college soccer at Davenport University.http://dupanthers.com/roster.aspx?rp_id=6521http://www.mlssoccer.com/news/article/2015/03/05/rookie- dzenan-catic-living-his-american-dream-philadelphia-union While at college, Catic played with USL PDL club Michigan Bucks during their 2014-15 season, where he scored 16 goals in 14 appearances.http://www.uslpdl.com/teams/2014/22344.html#STATS ===Professional=== On January 15, 2015, Catic was selected 31st overall in the 2015 MLS SuperDraft by Philadelphia Union.http://www.csnphilly.com/soccer- philadelphia-union/mls-draft-union-take-little-known-dzenan-catic He signed with the club on March 1, 2015. Catic was loaned to the Union's USL partner club Harrisburg City Islanders in March 2015.https://twitter.com/city_islanders/status/581954006525693952?lang=en-gb Catic signed with USL club Rio Grande Valley FC Toros on February 1, 2016. Catic opted to miss the 2017 season due to concussion.https://www.instagram.com/p/BTecfLAgWxX/ ==Personal== Catic is a dual citizen of the United States and Bosnia & Herzegovina.http://www.mlssoccer.com/players/dzenan-catic ==References== ==External links== * Category:1992 births Category:Living people Category:1.
